column5: Hi everyone, I thought I'd put up some fishing pictures from this winter. I've had a lot of fun fishing over the past 3 months...multiple days out on simcoe, a couple missions to BOQ, a weekend trip to Haliburton, and a week of bass fishing with my parents in Central Florida. The highlight for me was spending an afternoon teaching my mom to bass fish, and catching my biggest bass in the process. Enjoy:                       Thanks for looking, Brad
Nice fish! Are you on a golf course there? LOL
Golf,n and bass,n SWEET DEAL.  I see ya got one of those not so many whities.
Yeah, but without the golf! yep, just the one.
I use to golf at newcastle (many years ago). When all the players were off the course,I would hit the ponds and get some nice buckets.The owner had no prob,as long as I put them back.
Nice summary Brad well done. Beauty walleye in that one pic. And congrats on the pb bass.
Thank you Pidge, glad you liked it.
Nice patch of pictures looks like the fishing gods are smiling on you.   Art
Great report thanks for taking the time to put it together

Nice shots man.  Those bass are hogs!  But more importantly, is that ean early ice whittie from Simcoe?  Not to many of those hoisted this year.  I fished that exact spot many times this year and was skunked on them....
From one fan of southern fishing to another, thanks Art.  Thanks!  Thanks, and yeah, it was early season in about 95 FOW. A lucky catch, as it turned out.
Nice pix.  Thanx.  Looks like you had a very good season.  Bass in Florida  BONUS!

Thanks for sharing DD, thats what it is all about, family, friends, fishing, and trying to enjoy a part of every day.  Nice job, could almost see our old house inthe background of the whitie pic.  Cheers
Nice shooting...ahhhhhh what I wouldn't give to have a Walter that that one....
